'''Reiyosaki Shrine''' (零羊崎神社, pronounced *Hitsujisaki Jinja* or *Reiyosaki Jinja*) refers to two Shinto shrines located in {{ill|Ishinomaki|en|石巻市}}, {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|en|宮城県}}. Both are considered candidates for the {{ill|Myoujin Taisha|en|名神大社}} listed as "Reiyosaki Shrine" in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyocho|en|延喜式神名帳}}.

* {{ill|Reiyosaki Shrine (Ishinomaki Minato)|en|零羊崎神社 (石巻市湊)}} (*Hitsujisaki Jinja*) - Located in Minato, Ishinomaki City, Miyagi Prefecture. Formerly designated as a {{ill|Ken-sha|en|県社}}.
* {{ill|Reiyosaki Shrine (Ishinomaki Mano)|en|零羊崎神社 (石巻市真野)}} (*Reiyosaki Jinja*) - Located in Mano, Ishinomaki City, Miyagi Prefecture. Formerly designated as a {{ill|Son-sha|en|村社}}.

